INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES(96, 1, '2013-09-18 13:25:09', '2013-09-18 17:25:09', '<h3 class="faq-title">What is Thrive Frozen Nutrition?</h3>\r\n<div class="faq-answer">Thrive Frozen Nutrition is a specially formulated ice cream type product designed to provide additional nutrition to anyone that may need it. It can be used any time during the day or evening as a great tasting nutritious meal replacement or snack.</div>\r\n<h3 class="faq-title">What is the nutritional value of Thrive?</h3>\r\n<div class="faq-answer">Each Thrive cup contains at least 9 grams of protein, 3 grams of fiber, and 25% of the daily recommended amounts of 24 vitamins and minerals along with four different strains of probiotics.</div>\r\n<h3 class="faq-title">What makes Thrive Frozen Nutrition so special?</h3>\r\n<div class="faq-answer">Many people, including children, teenagers, adults, and seniors do not get the right amounts of daily nutritional values which their bodies need. The majority of nutritional supplements available to consumers today do not deliver nutritional value AND great taste. Thrive Frozen Nutrition has been developed to provide consumers with the right amount of nutrition in a great tasting, convenient, ice cream type product.</div>\r\n<h3 class="faq-title">Where can I buy Thrive Frozen Nutrition?</h3>\r\n<div class="faq-answer">Thrive Frozen Nutrition is in the process of being introduced into the market. Since it takes time for new products to reach the shelves of your local stores, Thrive recommends that you visit our website, www.thrive4nutrition.com for ordering information or call 1-855-376-9367.</div>\r\n<h3 class="faq-title">What is different about Thrive Frozen Nutrition when compared with liquid nutrition shakes?</h3>\r\n<div class="faq-answer">It tastes great and is fun to eat! It has been proven that people, especially those needing extra nutrition, enjoy ice cream type products because ice cream is fun to eat and people never seem to tire of eating ice cream. Our experience tells us that many consumers who currently take liquid nutrition shakes do not prefer the taste, and therefore stop using products over a period of time.</div>\r\n<h3 class="faq-title">Who should consume Thrive Frozen Nutrition?</h3>\r\n<div class="faq-answer">Any individual in need of additional nutrition, such as those who are in or recently released from the hospital, skilled nursing, or assisted living facilities. It is especially beneficial to those individuals who are suffering from flavor fatigue or unable to consume adequate nutrition through conventional methods. Children under 12 should consult a physician.</div>\r\n<h3 class="faq-title">When should someone consume Thrive Frozen Nutrition products?</h3>\r\n<div class="faq-answer">Thrive Frozen Nutrition products may be served as a great tasting nutritious meal replacement, “dessert,” or between meal snack.</div>\r\n<h3 class="faq-title">Is Thrive Frozen Nutrition effective at helping individuals maintain a healthy weight or gain weight?</h3>\r\n<div class="faq-answer">Consumers are more likely to maintain a healthy weight or gain weight when they enjoy the taste of the nutritious alternative they are using, because they are more likely to eat the product repeatedly. Thrive is the first of its kind product that is able to provide consumers with exceptional nutritional value in a great tasting, fun to eat product!</div>\r\n<h3 class="faq-title">Is Thrive Frozen Nutrition kosher?</h3>\r\n<div class="faq-answer">Yes, Thrive Frozen Nutrition is certified kosher through the Orthodox Union.</div>\r\n<h3 class="faq-title">Is Thrive Frozen Nutrition gluten free?</h3>\r\n<div class="faq-answer">Yes, all ingredients used in Thrive Frozen Nutrition are gluten free, therefore, the finished product is gluten free.</div>\r\n<h3 class="faq-title">What allergens are present in Thrive Frozen Nutrition?</h3>\r\n<div class="faq-answer">Thrive Homemade Vanilla contains Milk and Eggs. Thrive Milk Chocolate, Chocolate Fudge, and Strawberry contain Milk.</div>\r\n<h3 class="faq-title">Is Thrive Frozen Nutrition suitable for people who are lactose intolerant?</h3>\r\n<div class="faq-answer">Yes, Thrive Frozen Nutrition is suitable for individuals who are lactose intolerant. However, there are trace amounts of lactose in each cup due to the dairy products used. Each cup contains less than 0.5 grams of lactose.</div>\r\n<h3 class="faq-title">What flavors does Thrive Frozen Nutrition come in?</h3>\r\n<div class="faq-answer">Homemade Vanilla, Strawberry, Milk Chocolate, and Chocolate Fudge. THRIVE Homemade Vanilla is rich with Real Vanilla extract, eggs and custard flavors reminiscent of traditional homemade vanilla ice cream. THRIVE Strawberry is a fresh strawberry flavor made with strawberry puree, specially processed to keep the strawberries’ natural sweetness and flavor. THRIVE Milk Chocolate is a creamy milk chocolate made with mild premium cocoa and a touch of vanilla. THRIVE Chocolate Fudge is a chocolate reminiscent of indulgent dark chocolate ice cream. A true chocolate lovers delight.</div>\r\n<h3 class="faq-title">Why is Thrive Frozen Nutrition considered “Complete” nutrition?</h3>\r\n<div class="faq-answer">Thrive Frozen Nutrition is considered complete because it offers all of the key nutrients and in a balanced form. Thrive Frozen Nutrition contains 12% to 18% daily value of all the key nutrition components – fat, carbohydrates and protein. In this way the nutrition offered is balanced and complete. In addition to being balanced, Thrive Frozen Nutrition offers at least a 25% daily value for 24 vitamins and minerals as well as providing much needed probiotics and fiber. Because of the variety of nutritional components and the quantities of nutrition available in each cup, Thrive Frozen Nutrition is considered “complete” nutrition.</div>\r\n<h3 class="faq-title">How much protein does Thrive contain, and is this the protein amount I need to regain or maintain my health?</h3>\r\n<div class="faq-answer">Each Thrive cup contains nine grams of protein which has been proven to be the right amount of protein for consumers who require additional amounts of protein in their diet to regain weight and improve their health.</div>\r\n<h3 class="faq-title">What is the type of protein which is used in Thrive Frozen Nutrition?</h3>\r\n<div class="faq-answer">Milk protein isolate is the primary source of protein added. Additional protein may be in the product as a result of cream and flavor components. Milk protein is used because it does not have the same digestive issues as soy protein.</div>\r\n<h3 class="faq-title">Is Thrive a good source of fiber?</h3>\r\n<div class="faq-answer">Yes. Thrive is a good source of fiber because it contains a soluble dietary fiber, known as Fibersol-2, which has been proven by clinical studies to relieve occasional constipation.</div>\r\n<h3 class="faq-title">Can you tell me more about Fibersol-2?</h3>\r\n<div class="faq-answer">The primary source of fiber in Thrive Frozen Nutrition is a digestion resistant maltodextrin known as Fibersol-2. “Fibersol®-2 digestion resistant maltodextrin is a low viscosity soluble dietary fiber that clinical research has indicated helps support or maintain intestinal regularity. Clinical studies show that Fibersol®-2 helps to relieve occasional constipation, and select studies show that it improves stool consistency. Studies show that Fibersol®-2 digestion resistant maltodextrin when taken with a meal may attenuate the rise in serum glucose following the meal. Fibersol®-2 has the potential to reduce peak postprandial blood glucose and insulin levels that are within the normal range in healthy individuals. In addition, studies show that Fibersol®-2 does not alter healthy, steady-state blood glucose or insulin levels. Limited data also suggest that Fibersol®-2 digestion resistant maltodextrin when taken with a meal or food may attenuate the rise in serum triglycerides following the meal and that it may help retain healthy serum triglyceride levels.” (ADM/Matsutani, “Health Benefits.” Fibersol2.com).</div>\r\n<h3 class="faq-title">What is health benefits associated with the probiotic cultures found in Thrive Frozen Nutrition?/</h3>\r\n<div class="faq-answer">\r\n\r\n“A probiotic is a microorganism that contributes positively to the body’s health.” (Dr. Rick Swartzburg, D.C., “What is a Probiotic.” probiotic.org). Probiotics are found in the digestive tract of humans. Although there are numerous strains of probiotics commercially available, Thrive Frozen Nutrition cups contain S. thermophilus, L.bulgaricus, L. acidophilus, and Bifidobacterium. Each strain offers unique benefits to the consumer.Streptococcus thermophilus, or S. thermophilus, has been known to promote gastrointestinal health. This strain is unique in that it lacks the genes containing surface proteins. The lack of surface proteins do not allow the harmful bacteria to attach to the probiotic thus “hiding” from the body’s natural defenses (Dr. Rick Swartzburg, D.C., “Streptococcus Thermophilus,” probiotic.org).\r\n\r\nLactobacillus bulgaricus, or L. bulgaricus, has been shown to reduce intestinal infections. It does this be secreting acid, making it difficult for the pathogens to survive as well as preventing them from attacking to the mucous lining in the intestine. It also helps other beneficial microflora become established in the gut. As a result of the microflora flourishing, harmful pathogens are not allowed to flourish due to competition. “L. bulgaricus appears to play several important roles as a soldier in this battlefield of the digestive tract.” (Dr. Rick Swartzburg, D.C., “Lactobacillus Bulgaricus,” probiotic.org).\r\n\r\nLactobacillus acidophilus, or L. acidophilus, has also been shown to guard against infection and disease. It is especially helpful in digesting lactose and assisting in the absorption of certain vitamins and minerals. L. acidophilus produces the enzyme lactase which is instrumental in breaking down lactose, milk sugar, into a simple sugar. Because of this ability, L. acidophilus is beneficial to those individuals suffering from lactose intolerance. L. acidophilus also produces other enzymes which help increase the absorption rate of certain vitamins and minerals such as vitamin B, vitamin K, and calcium. (Dr. Rick Swartzburg, D.C., “Acidophilus,” probiotic.org).\r\n\r\nBifidobacterium is found naturally in the guts flora. Its primary purpose is to aid in the digestion of food. It has been shown to reduce some of the symptoms associated with Irritable Bowel Syndrome. (Dr. Rick Swartzburg, D.C., “Bifidobacterium,” probiotic.org).\r\n\r\nIn order for microbes such as S. thermophiles, L. bulgaricus, L. acidophilus, and Bifodobacterium to be effective in the body, they must be administered live, capable of surviving and growing throughout the digestion process and in beneficial quantities. (Dr. Rick Swartzburg, D.C., “The Leading Source Guide To Probiotics, Prebiotics, Yogurt, Acidophilus, Lactobacillus, Kefir and Other Sources of Friendly Bacteria and Yeast Organisms,” probiotic.org). Thrive Frozen Nutrition cups are able to provide probiotics due to the nature in which the products are manufactured. The probiotics are added to the product following the pasteurization, or bacteria destroying, step. This allows for the probiotics to be administered live. They are also added at a level that is considered beneficial.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<h3 class="faq-title">I currently take Ensure. Can I substitute Thrive for Ensure in my daily routine, and be confident that I will not give up any nutrition value?</h3>\r\n<div class="faq-answer">Thrive’s product formula has all the nutritional values of Ensure, plus probiotics which enhance digestive health. Thrive was especially designed to provide a great tasting ice cream type product which consumers will love to eat, and will not tire of our flavors over a long period of time.</div>\r\n<h3 class="faq-title">Do I need to consult a physician before I start using Thrive Frozen Nutrition?</h3>\r\n<div>Although it is not essential for you to get your physician to prescribe Thrive, it is always important to regularly consult your physician, particularly if you are not feeling normal, or are experiencing weight loss, or body weakness.</div>\r\n<h3 class="faq-title">How many cups of Thrive Frozen Nutrition can or should I consume each day?</h3>\r\n<div class="faq-answer">Thrive has been developed as a great tasting nutritional alternative to the liquid(s) you are already taking. If you are taking two containers of a liquid nutrition shakes each day, Thrive recommends you enjoy two cups of our product. Thrive should not be used as your only source of nutrition.</div>\r\n<h3 class="faq-title">What section of my grocery store would I expect to find Thrive?</h3>\r\n<div class="faq-answer">Most likely, Thrive will be found in the frozen food section or ice cream section of your local grocery store. If you can’t find Thrive in your store, please ask your store manager to order Thrive for you.</div>', 'FAQ', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '95-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-09-18 13:25:09', '2013-09-18 17:25:09', '', 95, 'http://thrive.dev.srginsight.com/2013/09/95-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
