INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES(148, 1, '2013-06-20 12:48:40', '2013-06-20 16:48:40', 'Dysphagia is a condition that causes mild to extreme difficulty swallowing and has many causes ranging from Gastroesophageal Reflux Disease (GERD) to stroke<sup><a href="http://www.webmd.com/digestive-disorders/tc/difficulty-swallowing-dysphagia-overview">1</a></sup>. Many of us have a friend or loved one who suffers from dysphagia - I have a good friend whose elderly mother Lucille suffers with this condition - which is actually what first sparked my interest in Thrive.\r\n\r\nWhen Lucille first came home from the long-term care facility, my friend was instructed to give her Ensure but to thicken it with a powdered thickener. I went one night to stay with Lucille and mixed up the Ensure + thickener concoction - WHAT A MESS! It did not look, smell or taste very appetizing and I did not blame Lucille for grumbling about drinking it. I noticed that night and on many occasions since then that she will drink about half of it then she does not want any more because she does not like it. We now had a new worry - that in addition to all of Lucille''s other health issues, she was not getting adequate nutrition. My friend was also having some distress over throwing away at least half of a bottle of Ensure several times a day - no one minds spending money to give Lucille everything she needs but it seems so wasteful to buy something for her that she does not like or want and that mostly ends up in the trash can.\r\n\r\nIt is well-known in my group of friends that Lucille loves ice cream - and struggle though she does to walk, she would get herself over to that freezer from time to time to make herself a little cup of it. We would fuss at her because while she enjoys ice cream and we want her to enjoy eating, it is not providing the complete nutrition she needs. Imagine my joy at discovering Thrive! Lucille''s favorite food with a <a title="Thrive Premium Ice Cream Formula" href="http://thriveicecream.com/our-story/thrive-formula">nutrition profile that matches Ensure</a> and does not require anything to be added for it to be easy and fun for her to eat!\r\n\r\nThe <a title="National Dysphagia Diet Standards" href="http://www.asha.org/Publications/leader/2003/031104/f031104c/#1">National Dysphagia Diet Standards (NDD) </a>define four categories of liquids based on their viscosity. The four levels are Thin (water, juice, coffee, milk), Nectar, Honey and Pudding. Nectar consistency liquids are the most common NDD thickness required for patients with dysphagia. Thrive was tested by an independent registered dietician to determine the NDD thickness. All flavors but the Chocolate Fudge were determined to have a Nectar consistency - the Chocolate Fudge was determined to be Honey consistency. Every individual''s needs vary on the thickness needed to make swallowing safe and comfortable (and of course, you should always check with your doctor if you have questions or concerns) but for Lucille, Thrive is exactly right - the Nectar consistency of the <a title="Homemade Vanilla" href="http://thriveicecream.com/products/vanilla">Homemade Vanilla</a> and <a title="Thrive Milk Chocolate" href="http://thriveicecream.com/milk-chocolate">Milk Chocolate</a> is exactly what her dietician recommends!\r\n\r\n<img class="alignleft" alt="A Thrive Ice Cream delivery to a friend with dysphagia" src="http://thriveicecream.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/Thrive_Delivery.png" width="350" height="263" />Yesterday, I packed up some Thrive and took it to Lucille. When I arrived, there was the half-finshed Ensure on her nightstand and she was fast asleep. Her daughter is so excited about the Thrive in her freezer because now, when Lucille sneaks over there to get ice cream while no one is looking, she will be getting ice cream with complete nutrition. And because Lucille LOVES ice cream, we know she will finish every bite and get ALL of the nutrition she needs every time she has a cup! Lucille did not wake up while I was there but I hope to update this post in the near future with a picture of Lucille enjoying her Homemade Vanilla and Milk Chocolate Thrive. If you or someone you know struggles with dysphagia, talk to your (or their) doctor about making Thrive part of your every-day routine - with all the protein of an egg, fiber, 24 vitamins and minerals, probiotics and a nectar consistency that makes it easy to swallow - Thrive is the a wonderful addition to anyone''s diet but most especially for those who struggle to get enough nutrition due to dysphagia.\r\n\r\n<a title="Where to Buy" href="http://thriveicecream.com/products/where-to-buy">Don''t forget to download your $1 off coupon for your next purchase of Thrive</a>\r\n\r\nTo Your Health!\r\nMelissa R., Thrive Ambassador', 'Dysphagia (Trouble Swallowing) and Thrive Ice Cream', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'dysphagia-trouble-swallowing-and-thrive-ice-cream', '', '', '2013-09-30 12:49:03', '2013-09-30 16:49:03', '', 0, 'http://thrive.dev.srginsight.com/?p=148', 0, 'post', '', 0);
