INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES(150, 1, '2013-06-25 12:49:50', '2013-06-25 16:49:50', 'Probiotics are suddenly trendy - while watching TV the other night, I saw an ad promoting a probiotic supplement no fewer than four times in 2 hours. There is a lot of buzz about the importance of probiotics to keeping your digestive system healthy and by extension, strengthening your immune system. The ad I saw for the supplement pointed out that about 70% of your immune system lives in your digestive tract - making digestive health critical to your health and well-being. <a title="The Probiotic Scoop" href="http://thriveicecream.com/the-scoop/the-probiotic-scoop">In our first article we discussed antibiotics and how they can unintentionally damage the beneficial bacteria that are your body''s major defense against disease</a>. In this article, we discuss some criteria for evaluating probiotic products for effectiveness.\r\n\r\nLet''s start with a basic definition of probiotics:\r\n\r\n<strong>"<a title="Annual Review of Food Science and Technology -  Food Formats for Effective Delivery of Probiotics" href="http://www.annualreviews.org/eprint/k7FW6TJKtWn27zBIBrRr/full/10.1146/annurev.food.080708.100743">Probiotics are live microorganisms, which when administered in adequate amounts confer a health benefit on the host</a>"</strong>\r\n\r\n<a title="Probiotic Information and Resources" href="http://probiotic.org">Probiotic.org</a>  reports that "Scientists are now even suggesting that the DNA of probiotic bacteria is more important than our cells’ DNA in predicting our vulnerabilities and possible future diseases." Probiotics are generally recognized for their immune and digestive health benefits, such as reduced side effects associated with antibiotic use, improved intestinal regularity, reduced symptoms associated with irritable bowel syndrome, and reduced gut inflammation and are increasingly recognized as helpful in reducing the incidence and effects of infectious diseases. <sup><a title="Annual Review of Food Science and Technology -  Food Formats for Effective Delivery of Probiotics" href="http://www.annualreviews.org/eprint/k7FW6TJKtWn27zBIBrRr/full/10.1146/annurev.food.080708.100743">1</a></sup>\r\n\r\n<img class="alignleft" alt="Thrive_Waffle_Bowl" src="http://thriveicecream.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/Thrive_Waffle_Bowl.png" width="316" height="238" />Probiotics are live cultures - when selecting a product with probiotics it is important to ensure that the cultures are still alive at the time of purchase. Probiotics delivered in liquid, pill or powder form are affected by exposure to oxygen and if not packaged properly, may be completely ineffective at the time of purchase. Although refrigeration of these products can help extend their shelf life, many if not most sit on warm store shelves for an unknown amount of time until you make your purchase, losing effectiveness with each passing day. If you are currently using one of these products, be aware that you may be receiving only a fraction of the advertised types and amounts of live cultures as a result. Delivering probiotics in a frozen nutrition product works really well because the freezing process actually prolongs the lives of the cultures. Because the cultures in Thrive are maintained in a frozen state until you open the cup, you can be sure you are receiving the full benefit of live, active cultures. The cultures defrost as they enter your digestive system, as fresh as the moment they were added!\r\n\r\nThe amount of live cultures in a product matters as well. Effective levels of probiotics are in the range of 100 million to 10 billion Colony Forming Units (CFU) per day. Thrive contains 2.9 billion CFU per serving of four probiotics that have been shown to be beneficial to digestive health and overall well-being:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>S.thermophilus</li>\r\n	<li>L.bulgaricus</li>\r\n	<li>L. acidophilus</li>\r\n	<li>Bifidobacterium</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nWhen evaluating a product that contains probiotics, be sure that:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>It contains an adequate amount of probiotics - a minimum of 100 million to 10 billion CFUs</li>\r\n	<li>The probiotics are delivered live</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThrive Ice Cream is an excellent way to deliver 20 BILLION CFUs of living cultures to your digestive system and comes in four delicious flavors - <a title="Homemade Vanilla" href="http://thriveicecream.com/products/vanilla">Homemade Vanilla</a>, <a title="Milk Chocolate" href="http://thriveicecream.com/products/milk-chocolate">Milk Chocolate</a>, <a title="Strawberry" href="http://thriveicecream.com/products/strawberry">Strawberry</a> and <a title="Chocolate Fudge" href="http://thriveicecream.com/products/chocolate-fudge">Chocolate Fudge</a>. In addition to plenty of the active cultures you need to promote good health, Thrive also contains protein, fiber and 24 vitamins and minerals - there has never been a more delicious way to stay healthy!\r\n\r\nIn my next article, I will provide in-depth information about each strain of active, live cultures in Thrive and how they work with your body to promote a healthy digestive and immune system.\r\n\r\n<a title="Where to Buy" href="http://thriveicecream.com/products/where-to-buy">Until then, don''t forget to grab your coupon for $1 off your next purchase of Thrive!</a>\r\n\r\nTo Your Health!\r\nMelissa R., Thrive Ambassador', 'Probiotics - Thrive has them!', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'probiotics-thrive-has-them', '', '\nhttp://thriveicecream.com/the-scoop/the-probiotic-scoop', '2013-09-30 12:57:24', '2013-09-30 16:57:24', '', 0, 'http://thrive.dev.srginsight.com/?p=150', 0, 'post', '', 0);
