INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES(158, 1, '2013-09-30 13:04:41', '2013-09-30 17:04:41', '<strong>ORLANDO, FL, October 1, 2013 ——</strong>Thrive Premium Ice Cream, producer of the nation’s leading nutritional ice cream product, has announced its sponsorship of the 2013 National Frozen &amp; Refrigerated Food Convention, (NFRA) October 19 – 22 in San Diego, CA with an exhibition space in the NFRA Café.\r\n“We’re truly thrilled to be here at the NFRA, especially given the association’s commitment to transform the frozen food conversation with its launch this year of the frozen food consumer awareness campaign,” said Frank Everett, Co-Founder, Thrive Premium Ice Cream. “While we work together as an industry to bring American back to the frozen food aisles, Thrive is committed to making a significant contribution to the health of the nation with our unique frozen nutrition carrier.”\r\nThrive is a win/win for retailers who want to grow their business through offering major new innovation with high level benefits, and consumers who might be seeking alternatives to the liquid nutritional shakes that have dominated the nutritional supplement market. Retailers across the country are starting to stock Thrive, including Publix, Hy-Vee, Meijer’s, Ahold Giant and others.\r\n<strong>Delivering Great Nutrition Without Sacrificing Taste</strong>\r\nIn its Dietary Guidelines for Americans the US Department of Health and Human Services notes that nearly 15 percent of American households have been unable to acquire adequate food to meet the recommended daily needs, while many other Americans consume less than optimal intake of certain nutrients despite having adequate resources for a healthy diet.\r\n\r\nThe majority of nutritional supplements available to consumers today delivers nutritional value but are severely lacking in taste. It has been proven that many consumers who currently take liquid nutrition shakes dislike the taste, therefore stop consuming the products which leads to a decrease in nutrient intake\r\n\r\nThe scientists behind Thrive Premium Ice Cream have developed a unique ice cream product that provides consumers with 25 percent of the daily recommended amounts of 24 vitamins and minerals, 9 grams of protein, 3 grams of fiber, and four different strains of probiotics.\r\n\r\nIce cream is an excellent carrier of nutrition, with a creamy satisfying texture and vitamins and minerals that have been carefully selected to coexist undetected. Unlike the liquid nutritional shakes that have dominated the nutritional supplement market and are made through a retort process (extreme heat), ice cream is made in a colder process that does not damage the vitamins, and maintains taste properties.\r\nAmerica’s favorite food can now be used to bring complete balanced nutrition to nearly anyone in need of extra nutrition or consumers who enjoy ice cream and might be looking for an alternative to portion controlled meals. Current available flavors include Homemade Vanilla, Strawberry, Milk Chocolate, and Chocolate Fudge, with new flavors as well as a sugar version in the works in coming months.\r\nThroughout the conference, attendees are invited to visit Thrive in the NFRA café to sample the ice cream and learn about the first ice cream product to deliver incredible taste while providing a source of complete and balanced nutrition. For more information on Thrive Premium Ice Cream please visit www.thriveicecream.com\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>About Thrive Premium Ice Cream</strong>\r\nThe Thrive Premium Ice Cream (www.thriveicecream.com) concept began almost a decade ago, with the idea of providing an ice cream product that packs nutrition into a great tasting form. Ice cream and dairy products are a natural carrier of great tasting nutrition such as proteins, calcium, vitamins and minerals. At the same time, ice cream is a favorite food of most Americans, generating revenues of $6.8 billion in take home sales.* an average of 48 pints of ice cream per person, per year. Thrive’s unique nutritional offerings and broad appeal make the premium ice cream a natural fit for added nutrition lacking in the diets of many consumers today. * Source: MarketLine, an Informa business.', 'Thrive at 2013 National Frozen & Refrigerated Food Convention', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'thrive-at-2013-national-frozen-refrigerated-food-convention', '', '', '2013-09-30 13:04:41', '2013-09-30 17:04:41', '', 0, 'http://thrive.dev.srginsight.com/?p=158', 0, 'post', '', 0);
