r person, per year. Thrive’s unique nutritional offerings and broad appeal make the premium ice cream a natural fit for added nutrition lacking in the diets of many consumers today. * Source: MarketLine, an Informa business.', 'Thrive at 2013 National Frozen & Refrigerated Food Convention', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '158-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-09-30 13:04:41', '2013-09-30 17:04:41', '', 158, 'http://thrive.dev.srginsight.com/2013/09/158-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES(160, 1, '2013-09-30 13:05:59', '2013-09-30 17:05:59', '<strong>ORLANDO, FL, October 1, 2013 ——</strong>Thrive Premium Ice Cream, producer of the nation’s leading nutritional ice cream product, has announced it will exhibit at the 2013 Food &amp; Nutrition Conference &amp; Expo (FNCE) October 19 – 22 in Houston, TX, at Booth # 662 in the Gluten Free Pavilion.\r\n\r\n“Thrive is carving out a new category in ice cream that instead of focusing on what’s been taken out of it, has defined Nutritious Ice Cream by what is being put in,” said Frank Everett, Co-Founder, Thrive Premium Ice Cream. “Nutrient deficiency is a growing problem in America today; we expect to make a significant contribution to the health of the nation with our unique nutrition carrier.”\r\n\r\nIn its Dietary Guidelines for Americans the US Department of Health and Human Services notes that nearly 15 percent of American households have been unable to acquire adequate food to meet the recommended daily needs, while many other Americans consume less than optimal intake of certain nutrients despite having adequate resources for a healthy diet.\r\n\r\nThe majority of nutritional supplements available to consumers today delivers nutritional value but are severely lacking in taste. It has been proven that many consumers who currently take liquid nutrition shakes dislike the taste, therefore stop consuming the products which leads to a decrease in nutrient intake\r\n\r\nThrive Premium Ice Cream: Delivering Great Nutrition Without Sacrificing Taste\r\nThe scientists behind Thrive Premium Ice Cream have developed a unique ice cream product that provides consumers with 25 percent of the daily recommended amounts of 24 vitamins and minerals, 9 grams of protein, 3 grams of fiber, and four different strains of probiotics.\r\n\r\nIce cream is an excellent carrier of nutrition, with a creamy satisfying texture and vitamins and minerals that have been carefully selected to coexist undetected. Unlike the liquid nutritional shakes that have dominated the nutritional supplement market and are made through a retort process (extreme heat), ice cream is made in a colder process that does not damage the vitamins, and maintains taste properties.\r\nAmerica’s favorite food can now be used to bring complete balanced nutrition to nearly anyone in need of extra nutrition or consumers who enjoy ice cream and might be looking for an alternative to portion controlled meals. Current available flavors include Homemade Vanilla, Strawberry, Milk Chocolate, and Chocolate Fudge, with new flavors as well as a sugar version in the works in coming months.\r\nThroughout the conference, attendees are invited to visit Thrive’s booth to sample the ice cream and learn about the first ice cream product to deliver incredible taste while providing a source of complete and balanced nutrition. For more information on Thrive Premium Ice Cream please visit FNCE Booth #662 In the Gluten Free Pavilion.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>About Thrive Premium Ice Cream</strong>\r\nThe Thrive Premium Ice Cream (www.thriveicecream.com) concept began almost a decade ago, with the idea of providing an ice cream product that packs nutrition into a great tasting form. Ice cream and dairy products are a natural carrier of great tasting nutrition such as proteins, calcium, vitamins and minerals. At the same time, ice cream is a favorite food of most Americans, generating revenues of $6.8 billion in take home sales.* an average of 48 pints of ice cream per person, per year. Thrive’s unique nutritional offerings and broad appeal make the premium ice cream a natural fit for added nutrition lacking in the diets of many consumers today. * Source: MarketLine, an Informa business.', 'Thrive at the 2013 Food and Nutrition Conference and Expo', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'thrive-at-the-2013-food-and-nutrition-conference-and-expo', '', '', '2013-09-30 13:05:59', '2013-09-30 17:05:59', '', 0, 'http://thri